<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="301" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">
Mexico (new country record, Chiapas), Guatemala, Honduras, Nicaragua, Costa Rica (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1947.tb01057.x" author="Balfour-Browne, J" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="425 - 448" refId="B14" refString="Balfour-Browne, J, 1947. A revision of the genus Bidessonotus Regimbart (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 98: 425 - 448, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1947.tb01057.x" title="A revision of the genus Bidessonotus Regimbart (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1947.tb01057.x" volume="98" year="1947">Balfour-Browne 1947</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.622.9155" author="Miller, KB" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="95 - 127" refId="B62" refString="Miller, KB, 2016. New species of Bidessonotus Regimbart, 1895 with a review of the South American species (Coleoptera, Adephaga, Dytiscidae, Hydroporinae, Bidessini). ZooKeys 622: 95 - 127, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.622.9155" title="New species of Bidessonotus Regimbart, 1895 with a review of the South American species (Coleoptera, Adephaga, Dytiscidae, Hydroporinae, Bidessini)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.622.9155" volume="622" year="2016">Miller 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nilsson, AN" journalOrPublisher="Dugesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" publicationUrl="http://www.waterbeetles.eu" refId="B75" refString="Nilsson, AN, Hajek, J, 2020. A World Catalogue of the Family Dytiscidae, or the Diving Beetles (Coleoptera, Adephaga). Version 1.I.2020. National Museum, Prague. http://www.waterbeetles.eu" title="A World Catalogue of the Family Dytiscidae, or the Diving Beetles (Coleoptera, Adephaga). Version 1. I. 2020. National Museum, Prague." url="http://www.waterbeetles.eu" year="2020">
Nilsson and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hájek">Hajek</normalizedToken>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). The species has been recorded from an altitude of ca. 122 m (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1947.tb01057.x" author="Balfour-Browne, J" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="425 - 448" refId="B14" refString="Balfour-Browne, J, 1947. A revision of the genus Bidessonotus Regimbart (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 98: 425 - 448, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1947.tb01057.x" title="A revision of the genus Bidessonotus Regimbart (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1947.tb01057.x" volume="98" year="1947">Balfour-Browne 1947</bibRefCitation>
), herein we recorded the species at level 4 (1,619 m).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
